  "prompt": "How is an IPS officers uniform different from other police officers?",
  "response": "IPS (Indian Police Service) officers have a distinct uniform that sets them apart from other police officers in India. Here are some key differences:\n\n1. Insignia: IPS officers wear distinct shoulder badges and epaulettes indicating their rank and service.\n\n2. Color: Their uniforms are typically more formal and can vary based on the occasion (ceremonial, field, or daily wear).\n\n3. Rank Indicators: The uniform includes specific badges and markings that indicate their IPS status and rank.\n\n4. Style: IPS uniforms are generally more tailored and sophisticated compared to state police uniforms.\n\n5. Accessories: They may wear additional accessories like peak caps or other formal headgear that distinguish them from local police officers.\n\nThe exact details can vary depending on the specific rank, occasion, and jurisdiction, but these are the general distinguishing features of an IPS officer's uniform.",
